U.S. Naval Academy STEM Center for Education and Outreach's Dr. Angela Moran, the "Mother of USNA STEM," recently retired after 27 years of teaching!

She taught them about the endless possibilities of the world around them and encouraged everyone to believe in themselves.

#USNASTEM #WomeninSTEM

Chief of Naval Operations Adm. Mike Gilday @usnavycno issued a statement to the Fleet yesterday regarding the service members killed in Afghanistan on August 26: 

“This is a solemn day for the @usnavy and @marines team. Those warriors who died gave their lives to save thousands of men, women, and children, Americans, and Afghans alike. Their courage and selflessness represent the highest ideals of America. We pay solemn tribute to their sacrifice. To the families and loved ones who grieve – you are not alone. We stand beside you in this pain, humbled by the loss of these heroes, grateful that individuals of such valor chose to serve among us.“

#BlueGreenTeam

“2 for 7” signing is in the books! ✍️

#USNA2023 signed their “2 for 7” contracts last week when they returned to the Yard for the start of their 2/C year. 

The “2 for 7” contract marks the successful completion of a midshipman’s first two years at #USNA, as well as their commitment to the next seven years of service
- two additional years at the Academy, followed by five years as #sailors or #marines. 

#GoNavy #USNavy

🎥: MC3 Bonaparte
